## Wireshark

Wireshark is a network protocol analyzer used to capture and inspect network packets in real time.

During this lab, I captured live traffic generated from my own system and analyzed different protocols.

---

# Filters Practiced

## DNS

```text
dns
```

Displays only DNS packets.

---

## TCP

```text
tcp
```

Displays all TCP packets.

---

## ICMP

```text
icmp
```

Displays ICMP packets such as Ping requests and replies.

---

## TLS

```text
tls
```

Displays encrypted HTTPS traffic.

---

## HTTPS (TCP Port 443)

```text
tcp.port == 443
```

Shows encrypted HTTPS communication.

---

## DNS Queries Only

```text
dns.flags.response == 0
```

Displays only DNS requests.

---

